  "prompt": "Which US credit card charges no foreign transaction fees?",
  "response": "There are many US credit cards that charge no foreign transaction fees. Here are some popular options, categorized for easier browsing:\n\n**General Travel Rewards Cards:**\n\n*   **Chase Sapphire Preferred Card:**  Popular for its travel rewards and reasonable annual fee.\n*   **Chase Sapphire Reserve Card:**  Premium travel card with excellent benefits, but a higher annual fee.\n*   **Capital One Venture Rewards Credit Card:**  Simple rewards structure, good for those who want flexibility.\n*   **Capital One Venture X Rewards Credit Card:** A premium card with excellent travel benefits and credits that offset the annual fee.\n*   **American Express Gold Card:** Earns high rewards on dining and groceries, great for foodies.\n*   **American Express Platinum Card:**  Premium travel card with extensive benefits, but a high annual fee.\n*   **Bank of America Premium Rewards Credit Card:** Offers a solid rewards rate and benefits for Bank of America Preferred Rewards members.\n*   **Citi Premier Card:** Offers a good rewards rate on travel, dining, and gas.\n\n**Hotel Rewards Cards:**\n\n*   **Marriott Bonvoy Boundless Credit Card (Chase):** Earns Marriott Bonvoy points and offers free night awards.\n*   **World of Hyatt Credit Card (Chase):** Earns World of Hyatt points and offers free night awards.\n*   **Hilton Honors American Express Aspire Card:**  Premium Hilton card with top-tier status and lots of perks.\n*   **Hilton Honors American Express Surpass Card:** Mid-tier Hilton card with good earning rates and benefits.\n\n**Airline Rewards Cards:**\n\n*   **Delta SkyMiles Reserve American Express Card:** Premium Delta card with Sky Club access and Medallion Qualifying Dollar boosts.\n*   **United Explorer Card (Chase):** Earns United MileagePlus miles and offers priority boarding and free checked bag.\n\n**Cash Back Cards:**\n\n*   **Capital One Quicksilver Cash Rewards Credit Card:**  Simple, flat-rate cash back with no annual fee.\n*   **Capital One SavorOne Cash Rewards Credit Card:** Earns bonus rewards on dining, entertainment, streaming services, and groceries.\n*   **Discover it Chrome Gas & Restaurant Rewards:** Good for gas and restaurant spending.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Annual Fee:** Consider whether the annual fee is worth the benefits you'll receive, especially if you don't travel often.\n*   **Rewards Program:**  Choose a card with a rewards program that aligns with your spending habits and travel preferences.  Do you prefer cash back, travel points/miles, or hotel/airline specific points?\n*   **Credit Score:**  Most of these cards require a good to excellent credit score.\n*   **Specific Benefits:**  Compare the specific benefits of each card, such as travel insurance, purchase protection, and rental car insurance.\n*   **Foreign Transaction Fees:**  **Always double-check the terms and conditions** of any card before applying to ensure it truly has no foreign transaction fees.  While the cards listed above are generally known to have this feature, policies can change. Look for wording like \"0% foreign transaction fee\" or \"no foreign transaction fees.\"\n\n**How to Find More Options and Verify:**\n\n1.  **Use Online Credit Card Comparison Tools:** Websites like CreditCards.com, NerdWallet, and The Points Guy have filters to search for cards with no foreign transaction fees.\n2.  **Check Card Issuer Websites:** Browse the websites of major card issuers like Chase, Capital One, American Express, Citi, and Bank of America.\n3.  **Read the Card Agreement:** Before applying for any credit card, carefully read the card agreement (terms and conditions) to confirm the lack of foreign transaction fees and understand all other terms and conditions.\n\nBy doing your research and considering your individual needs and spending habits, you can find the best US credit card with no foreign transaction fees for your situation.\n",
